Defendant in custody appearing from Ozaukee County Jail.
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 10-05-2020.
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of eight (8) years. Three (3) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.  This will run concurrent with any other sentence presently being served.  
Conditions of extended supervision: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) Maintain full-time employment/schooling/job search combination; 
3) AODA assessment and follow through; 
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Have no contact with Tim Rohr or his residence; 
6) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) Pay costs of action; 
Defendant has credit for 349 days in this file. 
The defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but he is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.  
